    {
      "id": "FaL3WpZ1vk_0oP5W7xVa1",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 3313.3085270739543,
      "y": 4518.883319704199,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffffff",
      "fillStyle": "hachure",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "c0056",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1366016123,
      "version": 433,
      "versionNonce": 939753524,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1782273819912,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "width": 813.3162119698725,
      "height": 175,
      "text": "Two privileged branches past the fork — {Rot, Rot}: distinct-SAID events at\nthe same serial. >=2 privileged branches -> terminal; no repair resolves it\n(can't archive a privileged event, can't extend the other branch). The two\nseals share one previousSeal -> a single visible fork on the spine.\neffective-SAID = disputed:{prefix} -> reincept. {Rot, Rot} also reveals the\none preimage from the prior seal (reserve compromise); {Evl, Evl} is terminal\nthe same way but is not a reserve-compromise proof.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "center",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Two privileged branches past the fork — {Rot, Rot}: distinct-SAID events at\nthe same serial. >=2 privileged branches -> terminal; no repair resolves it\n(can't archive a privileged event, can't extend the other branch). The two\nseals share one previousSeal -> a single visible fork on the spine.\neffective-SAID = disputed:{prefix} -> reincept. {Rot, Rot} also reveals the\none preimage from the prior seal (reserve compromise); {Evl, Evl} is terminal\nthe same way but is not a reserve-compromise proof.",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
